               <l>tonight      I started walking back to you father</l>
               <l>it was meant to be a stroll but then I started</l> 
               <l>walking faster      father      I started chanting all</l>
               <l>the names of all the men I ever went to bed</l>
               <l>with      father      my thighs were burning and my feet</l>
               <l>were heavy with blood but I kept the pace and chants</l>
               <l>of names up      father      listed them to fence posts</l>
               <l>and the trees and didnâ€™t stop and started getting</l>
               <l>younger      father      and walked all night till I was home</l>
               <l>just a spark in your groin again and told you not</l>
               <l>to bring me back to life      told you I repented</l>
               <l>every name and had freed them of me      father</l>
         
                 
